A Pegasus Airlines jet was evacuated after landing at Germany's Düsseldorf Airport on Saturday when airport ground crew noticed one of its wheels was on fire, according to airport authorities. The plane had been carrying 163 passengers from Istanbul in Turkey to the western German city. Passengers were ordered by the pilot to evacuate using the emergency slides. There were no injuries reported. According to the website, FlightAware, the aircraft was an Airbus A320. Read more: Turkey: Scores injured after plane skids off runway, splits into three The fire reportedly extinguished itself before fire crews reached the plane. There was no immediate cause given for what caused the wheel to catch fire The incident is the second involving Turkey-based Pegasus Airlines this month. On February 5, a Pegasus Boeing 737 skidded off a runway at Istanbul's Sabiha Gokcen airport killing three people. An investigation into the Istanbul crash is ongoing. Send  Facebook   Twitter   google+   Whatsapp   Tumblr   linkedin   stumble   Digg   reddit   Newsvine Permalink https://p.dw.com/p/3XKtH wmr/mm (dpa, AP) DW sends out a selection of the day's news and features. Sign up here.